entry.def: If you overspend, you spend more money than you can afford to.

example.ex: Don't overspend on your home and expect to get the money back when you sell...
example.tran: 不要在买房子上超支并指望以后出售时还能把钱赚回来。

example.ex: I overspent by £1 on your shopping so I'm afraid you owe me...
example.tran: 我为你买的东西多付了1英镑，所以呢，恐怕你欠我的。

entry.def: If an organization or business has an overspend, it spends more money than was planned or allowed in its budget.

example.ex: Efforts are under way to avoid a £800,000 overspend.
example.tran: 正在采取措施以避免出现80万英镑的超支。
